This paper deals with reasoning in Bayesian belief networks, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses techniques for pruning irrelevant parts of a network, which is related to data structures (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper reports empirical tests, which could fall under social and information networks (cs.SI).
